{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Analyse Exploratoire\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Import des modules\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Analyse exploratoire\n",
    "\n",
    "L’objectif de cette partie est de comprendre la structure du jeu de données, d’identifier les variables utiles, de nettoyer les incohérences et de produire des premières analyses descriptives.\n",
    "\n",
    "Dans ce projet, nous travaillons sur les consommations énergétiques des bâtiments de Seattle, avec un focus sur les bâtiments **non résidentiels**.\n",
    "Comme deux fichiers CSV sont disponibles, nous commençons par les charger, les harmoniser puis les fusionner afin de disposer d’une base unique exploitable.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Import des bibliothèques\n",
    "\n",
    "Cette cellule importe les bibliothèques nécessaires à l’analyse :\n",
    "- **pandas** et **numpy** pour la manipulation des données ;\n",
    "- **matplotlib** et **seaborn** pour les visualisations ;\n",
    "- **sklearn** pour les futures étapes de modélisation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Quelques réglages d’affichage sont également ajoutés pour faciliter la lecture des résultats dans le notebook.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 99,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import sklearn\n",
    "\n",
    "pd.set_option(\"display.max_columns\", 100)\n",
    "sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Placeholders pour calmer Pylance dans le notebook\n",
    "building_consumption = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "pivot_energy = pd.DataFrame()\n",
    "pivot_property = pd.DataFrame()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Analyse Exploratoire\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Chargement des deux jeux de données\n",
    "\n",
    "Nous chargeons ici :\n",
    "- un fichier détaillé pour l’année **2016** ;\n",
    "- un fichier historique couvrant **2015 à aujourd’hui**.\n",
    "\n",
    "L’idée est de construire un jeu de données enrichi permettant à la fois :\n",
    "- une analyse détaillée sur 2016 ;\n",
    "- une vision plus large dans le temps grâce au fichier historique.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 100,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(38075, 52)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "path_2016 = \"data/2016_Building_Energy_Benchmarking.csv\"\n",
    "path_hist = \"data/Building_Energy_Benchmarking_Data,_2015-Present_20260316.csv\"\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2016 = pd.read_csv(path_2016, low_memory=False)\n",
    "df_hist = pd.read_csv(path_hist, low_memory=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "rename_2016 = {\n",
    "    \"PropertyName\": \"BuildingName\",\n",
    "    \"PrimaryPropertyType\": \"EPAPropertyType\",\n",
    "    \"PropertyGFABuilding(s)\": \"PropertyGFABuildings\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "df_2016 = df_2016.rename(columns=rename_2016)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2016[\"source_file\"] = \"2016_detail\"\n",
    "df_hist[\"source_file\"] = \"2015_present\"\n",
    "\n",
    "all_columns = sorted(set(df_2016.columns).union(set(df_hist.columns)))\n",
    "df_2016 = df_2016.reindex(columns=all_columns)\n",
    "df_hist = df_hist.reindex(columns=all_columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = pd.concat([df_2016, df_hist], ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(building_consumption.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Harmonisation des noms de colonnes\n",
    "\n",
    "Les deux fichiers n’utilisent pas exactement les mêmes noms de variables.\n",
    "Avant de les fusionner, il est donc nécessaire de rendre leur structure cohérente.\n",
    "\n",
    "Par exemple :\n",
    "- `PropertyName` peut devenir `BuildingName`,\n",
    "- `PrimaryPropertyType` peut être alignée avec `EPAPropertyType`,\n",
    "- `PropertyGFABuilding(s)` peut être harmonisée avec `PropertyGFABuildings`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Cette étape évite de perdre des colonnes ou de générer des erreurs lors de la concaténation.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 101,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Colonnes harmonisées : {'EPAPropertyType': 'PrimaryPropertyType', 'BuildingName': 'PropertyName', 'PropertyGFABuildings': 'PropertyGFABuilding(s)'}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rename_standard = {\n",
    "    \"EPAPropertyType\": \"PrimaryPropertyType\",\n",
    "    \"BuildingName\": \"PropertyName\",\n",
    "    \"PropertyGFABuildings\": \"PropertyGFABuilding(s)\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "cols_presentes = {\n",
    "    old: new\n",
    "    for old, new in rename_standard.items()\n",
    "    if old in building_consumption.columns\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = building_consumption.rename(columns=cols_presentes, errors=\"ignore\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Colonnes harmonisées :\", cols_presentes)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 102,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Colonnes harmonisées : {}\n",
      "['PrimaryPropertyType']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rename_standard = {\n",
    "    \"EPAPropertyType\": \"PrimaryPropertyType\",\n",
    "    \"BuildingName\": \"PropertyName\",\n",
    "    \"PropertyGFABuildings\": \"PropertyGFABuilding(s)\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "cols_presentes = {\n",
    "    old: new\n",
    "    for old, new in rename_standard.items()\n",
    "    if old in building_consumption.columns\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = building_consumption.rename(columns=cols_presentes, errors=\"ignore\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Colonnes harmonisées :\", cols_presentes)\n",
    "print([c for c in building_consumption.columns if \"PropertyType\" in c])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 103,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rename_2016 = {\n",
    "    \"PropertyName\": \"BuildingName\",\n",
    "    \"PrimaryPropertyType\": \"EPAPropertyType\",\n",
    "    \"PropertyGFABuilding(s)\": \"PropertyGFABuildings\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2016 = df_2016.rename(columns=rename_2016).copy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Conversion des colonnes numériques\n",
    "\n",
    "Certaines colonnes du fichier historique peuvent être lues comme du texte alors qu’elles représentent des valeurs numériques.\n",
    "\n",
    "Cette étape permet de :\n",
    "- supprimer les éventuelles virgules ou espaces parasites ;\n",
    "- convertir les colonnes concernées en format numérique ;\n",
    "- gérer proprement les valeurs manquantes.\n",
    "\n",
    "Cela est indispensable avant toute analyse statistique ou modélisation.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 104,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "numeric_cols = [\n",
    "    \"OSEBuildingID\", \"DataYear\", \"CouncilDistrictCode\", \"Latitude\", \"Longitude\",\n",
    "    \"YearBuilt\", \"NumberofBuildings\", \"NumberofFloors\", \"ENERGYSTARScore\",\n",
    "    \"PropertyGFATotal\", \"PropertyGFAParking\", \"PropertyGFABuildings\",\n",
    "    \"LargestPropertyUseTypeGFA\", \"SecondLargestPropertyUseTypeGFA\",\n",
    "    \"ThirdLargestPropertyUseTypeGFA\", \"Electricity(kWh)\", \"Electricity(kBtu)\",\n",
    "    \"NaturalGas(therms)\", \"NaturalGas(kBtu)\", \"SteamUse(kBtu)\",\n",
    "    \"SiteEUI(kBtu/sf)\", \"SiteEUIWN(kBtu/sf)\", \"SourceEUI(kBtu/sf)\",\n",
    "    \"SourceEUIWN(kBtu/sf)\", \"SiteEnergyUse(kBtu)\", \"SiteEnergyUseWN(kBtu)\",\n",
    "    \"TotalGHGEmissions\", \"GHGEmissionsIntensity\", \"SelfReportGFATotal\",\n",
    "    \"SelfReportGFABuildings\", \"SelfReportParking\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "def clean_numeric_columns(df, cols):\n",
    "    df = df.copy()\n",
    "    for col in cols:\n",
    "        if col in df.columns:\n",
    "            df[col] = (\n",
    "                df[col].astype(str)\n",
    "                .str.replace(\",\", \"\", regex=False)\n",
    "                .str.strip()\n",
    "                .replace({\"nan\": np.nan, \"None\": np.nan, \"\": np.nan})\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            df[col] = pd.to_numeric(df[col], errors=\"coerce\")\n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2016 = clean_numeric_columns(df_2016, numeric_cols)\n",
    "df_hist = clean_numeric_columns(df_hist, numeric_cols)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Fusion des fichiers et suppression des doublons\n",
    "\n",
    "Après harmonisation, les deux jeux de données sont concaténés dans une seule table appelée `building_consumption`.\n",
    "\n",
    "Comme le fichier historique contient déjà l’année 2016, il peut exister des doublons pour un même bâtiment et une même année.\n",
    "Nous supprimons donc les doublons en conservant en priorité la version la plus détaillée du fichier 2016.\n",
    "\n",
    "Cette étape garantit que chaque couple **bâtiment / année** n’apparaît qu’une seule fois.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 105,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(34881, 52)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df_2016[\"source_file\"] = \"2016_detail\"\n",
    "df_hist[\"source_file\"] = \"2015_present\"\n",
    "\n",
    "all_columns = sorted(set(df_2016.columns).union(set(df_hist.columns)))\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2016 = df_2016.reindex(columns=all_columns)\n",
    "df_hist = df_hist.reindex(columns=all_columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = pd.concat([df_2016, df_hist], ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "source_priority = {\n",
    "    \"2016_detail\": 0,\n",
    "    \"2015_present\": 1\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption[\"source_priority\"] = building_consumption[\"source_file\"].map(source_priority)\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = (\n",
    "    building_consumption\n",
    "    .sort_values([\"OSEBuildingID\", \"DataYear\", \"source_priority\"])\n",
    "    .drop_duplicates(subset=[\"OSEBuildingID\", \"DataYear\"], keep=\"first\")\n",
    "    .drop(columns=\"source_priority\")\n",
    "    .reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(building_consumption.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 106,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Avant déduplication : (38075, 52)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "all_columns = sorted(set(df_2016.columns).union(set(df_hist.columns)))\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2016 = df_2016.reindex(columns=all_columns)\n",
    "df_hist = df_hist.reindex(columns=all_columns)\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = pd.concat([df_2016, df_hist], ignore_index=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Avant déduplication :\", building_consumption.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 107,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Après déduplication : (34881, 52)\n",
