     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "source_priority = {\n",
    "    \"2016_detail\": 0,\n",
    "    \"2015_present\": 1\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption[\"source_priority\"] = building_consumption[\"source_file\"].map(source_priority)\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = (\n",
    "    building_consumption\n",
    "    .sort_values([\"OSEBuildingID\", \"DataYear\", \"source_priority\"])\n",
    "    .drop_duplicates(subset=[\"OSEBuildingID\", \"DataYear\"], keep=\"first\")\n",
    "    .drop(columns=\"source_priority\")\n",
    "    .reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Après déduplication :\", building_consumption.shape)\n",
    "print(building_consumption[\"DataYear\"].value_counts().sort_index())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Standardisation finale des noms de variables\n",
    "\n",
    "Une fois les données fusionnées, nous renommons certaines colonnes afin de conserver un schéma clair et stable dans tout le notebook.\n",
    "\n",
    "L’objectif est de travailler ensuite avec des noms uniques, cohérents et faciles à réutiliser dans les cellules d’analyse et de modélisation.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 108,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Colonnes renommées : {'EPAPropertyType': 'PrimaryPropertyType', 'BuildingName': 'PropertyName', 'PropertyGFABuildings': 'PropertyGFABuilding(s)'}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rename_standard = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"EPAPropertyType\" in building_consumption.columns and \"PrimaryPropertyType\" not in building_consumption.columns:\n",
    "    rename_standard[\"EPAPropertyType\"] = \"PrimaryPropertyType\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"BuildingName\" in building_consumption.columns and \"PropertyName\" not in building_consumption.columns:\n",
    "    rename_standard[\"BuildingName\"] = \"PropertyName\"\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"PropertyGFABuildings\" in building_consumption.columns and \"PropertyGFABuilding(s)\" not in building_consumption.columns:\n",
    "    rename_standard[\"PropertyGFABuildings\"] = \"PropertyGFABuilding(s)\"\n",
    "\n",
    "building_consumption = building_consumption.rename(columns=rename_standard)\n",
    "print(\"Colonnes renommées :\", rename_standard)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 109,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if \"EPAPropertyType\" in building_consumption.columns and \"PrimaryPropertyType\" not in building_consumption.columns:\n",
    "    building_consumption = building_consumption.rename(columns={\"EPAPropertyType\": \"PrimaryPropertyType\"})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Filtrage des bâtiments pertinents\n",
    "\n",
    "Le projet porte uniquement sur les **bâtiments non résidentiels**.\n",
    "Nous excluons donc les bâtiments multifamiliaux afin de rester cohérents avec l’objectif métier.\n",
    "\n",
    "Nous conservons ici les catégories suivantes :\n",
    "- `NonResidential`\n",
    "- `Nonresidential COS`\n",
    "- `SPS-District K-12`\n",
    "- `Campus`\n",
    "\n",
    "Ce filtrage permet de concentrer l’analyse sur les bâtiments comparables du point de vue de leur usage.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 110,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(14714, 52)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "non_residential_types = [\n",
    "    \"NonResidential\",\n",
    "    \"Nonresidential COS\",\n",
    "    \"SPS-District K-12\",\n",
    "    \"Campus\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "df = building_consumption[\n",
    "    building_consumption[\"BuildingType\"].isin(non_residential_types)\n",
    "].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"ComplianceStatus\" in df.columns:\n",
    "    df = df[df[\"ComplianceStatus\"] == \"Compliant\"].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "if \"DefaultData\" in df.columns:\n",
    "    df = df[df[\"DefaultData\"].fillna(False) == False].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 111,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df[\"UsageType\"] = np.where(\n",
    "    df[\"SecondLargestPropertyUseType\"].isna(),\n",
    "    \"Mono-usage\",\n",
    "    \"Multi-usages\"\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. Tables pivots de synthèse\n",
    "\n",
    "Les tables pivots permettent de résumer rapidement les données selon différentes dimensions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Nous construisons notamment :\n",
    "- une table des consommations et émissions moyennes par **année** et **type de bâtiment** ;\n",
    "- une table des consommations moyennes par **année** et **type principal de propriété** ;\n",
    "- une table de **comptage** du nombre de bâtiments par catégorie.\n",
    "\n",
    "Ces tableaux donnent une première vue d’ensemble sur la structure du dataset fusionné.\n"
   ]
  },
